<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><title>TechMyMoney Upgrade Execution Checklist</title></head><body>
<h1>TechMyMoney Upgrade Execution Checklist (Blue/Green)</h1>
<p><b>Date:</b> 2026-02-17<br><b>Prepared for:</b> mjcity0076@gmail.com, michael@techmymoney.com</p>

<h2>Downtime Estimate</h2>
<ul>
<li><b>Expected user-impact window:</b> 10-30 minutes (during final content freeze + DNS cutover)</li>
<li><b>DNS propagation variance:</b> 5 minutes to 4 hours depending on resolver cache</li>
<li><b>Rollback window:</b> immediate (switch DNS back to old VM) if issues appear</li>
</ul>

<h2>Preflight (No Downtime)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Record current live state
<pre>
# From your admin machine
nslookup techmymoney.com
nslookup www.techmymoney.com
curl -I https://www.techmymoney.com
</pre>
</li>
<li>Create recovery snapshot on old VM (<b>wordpress-1-vm</b>)
<pre>
# On old VM
TS=$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S)
mkdir -p ~/rollback-safety-$TS
sudo cp /var/www/html/wp-config.php ~/rollback-safety-$TS/
sudo tar -C /var/www/html -czf ~/rollback-safety-$TS/wp-content-$TS.tar.gz wp-content
mysqldump -u root -p bitnami_wordpress > ~/rollback-safety-$TS/db-$TS.sql
</pre>
</li>
<li>Build new VM (Bitnami WordPress latest) in same region/zone family</li>
<li>Reserve/confirm static external IP for new VM</li>
</ol>

<h2>Stage New VM (No Downtime)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Verify services
<pre>
sudo /opt/bitnami/ctlscript.sh status
</pre>
</li>
<li>Copy site files from old VM to new VM
<pre>
# Run from old VM (or intermediary host with SSH access)
rsync -avz --progress /var/www/html/wp-content/ USER@NEW_VM_IP:/tmp/wp-content/
</pre>
</li>
<li>Import database dump to new VM
<pre>
# On new VM
mysql -u root -p bitnami_wordpress < /path/to/db.sql
</pre>
</li>
<li>Set ownership/permissions on new VM
<pre>
sudo chown -R bitnami:daemon /opt/bitnami/wordpress
sudo find /opt/bitnami/wordpress -type d -exec chmod 775 {} \;
sudo find /opt/bitnami/wordpress -type f -exec chmod 664 {} \;
</pre>
</li>
<li>Update WP URL if needed (staging check)
<pre>
wp option get home --allow-root
wp option get siteurl --allow-root
</pre>
</li>
</ol>

<h2>Compatibility Gate (Must Pass Before Cutover)</h2>
<ul>
<li>Homepage loads</li>
<li>Top navigation/category pages load</li>
<li>At least 3 recent posts render correctly</li>
<li>wp-admin login works</li>
<li>Plugin critical paths work (forms, cache, SEO, analytics)</li>
<li>Media loads from wp-content/uploads</li>
<li>HTTPS works and cert valid for techmymoney.com + www</li>
<li>No fatal PHP errors in logs</li>
</ul>

<h3>Validation commands</h3>
<pre>
curl -I http://NEW_VM_IP
curl -I https://www.techmymoney.com
sudo tail -n 200 /opt/bitnami/apache2/logs/error_log
sudo tail -n 200 /opt/bitnami/php/var/log/www-error.log
</pre>

<h2>Cutover Procedure (Downtime Window Starts)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Content freeze announcement (10-15 min)</li>
<li>Final delta sync from old VM
<pre>
# Old VM
mysqldump -u root -p bitnami_wordpress > /tmp/final.sql
rsync -avz --delete /var/www/html/wp-content/ USER@NEW_VM_IP:/tmp/wp-content/
</pre>
</li>
<li>Import final DB delta on new VM</li>
<li>Switch DNS A records in Squarespace
<ul>
<li>@ -> NEW_VM_IP</li>
<li>www -> NEW_VM_IP</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>Verify authoritative DNS
<pre>
for ns in ns-cloud-c1.googledomains.com ns-cloud-c2.googledomains.com ns-cloud-c3.googledomains.com ns-cloud-c4.googledomains.com; do
  echo "-- $ns"; dig +short @$ns techmymoney.com A; dig +short @$ns www.techmymoney.com A;
done
</pre>
</li>
</ol>

<h2>Post-Cutover Validation (First 30 Minutes)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Homepage + wp-login + wp-admin checks</li>
<li>Create one test post (draft) + media upload test</li>
<li>Verify server logs for fatal errors</li>
<li>Check SSL and redirect behavior</li>
<li>Monitor for 30 minutes</li>
</ol>

<h2>Rollback Plan (If anything fails)</h2>
<ol>
<li>Immediately revert Squarespace A records to old VM IP</li>
<li>Confirm authoritative DNS</li>
<li>Re-test homepage/wp-admin</li>
<li>Keep new VM for debugging, do not delete immediately</li>
</ol>

<h2>Cost-Control Cleanup</h2>
<ul>
<li>After 24-48h stable on new VM, stop old VM</li>
<li>After 7 days stable, snapshot old VM then delete</li>
</ul>

<h2>Notes from Previous Incident</h2>
<ul>
<li>Avoid rapid DNS toggles; they create stale-cache confusion.</li>
<li>Use authoritative nameserver checks as source of truth.</li>
<li>Apply one change at a time with timestamped logs.</li>
</ul>

</body></html>